content: That's really helpful, thanks! I do have some student loans, about $300 a month. I've saved up around $20,000 for a down payment and I'm willing to use some of my other savings for additional costs. My credit score is pretty good, around 750. I'm thinking of a 30-year fixed-rate mortgage. I don't have any other significant expenses besides my daily commute costs. And I was thinking of spending around $400,000 to $450,000 on a condo.
